    "Melchior came from an old wealthy family who hoped he would become a scientist and his older brother, <a href=\"/boisserees\">Sulpiz Boisser\u00e9e</a>, run the family business.": [],
    "The two were raised during the Napoleonic occupation of Cologne.": [],
    "Through his friend <a href=\"/bertramb\">Johann B. Bertram</a> he and Sulpiz became interested in art and especially that of the medieval era, a period well represented by the so-called Cologne school of painting, though much under appreciated.": [],
    "A family inheritance enabled the brothers to study the art monuments, traveling to the Netherlands and France.": [],
    "In 1803 they studied at the Mus\u00e9e Napoleon, (i.e., Louvre Museum, which had been greatly expanded through Napoleon's looted art from other countries).": [
