    "They watched, however, as many works of art they could not buy, architecture for example, be destroyed before them.": [],
    "In 1810 the brothers publicly displayed their collection in a baroque palace on Karl's Square, Heidelberg, in one of the early attempts both to interest the public in medieval art and publicize a collection.": [],
